cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on the task of single-image super-resolution with the presence of motion blur. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for this task, which involves training and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method in enhancing the image quality, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
